# AVCaptureOutput.DataDroppedReason.lateData

**Case**

The system dropped data because you’ve configured capture output to drop data when delegate queue is in a blocked state, and there’s data to deliver.

## Declaration

```swift
case lateData
```

## Discussion

Use the [doc://com.apple.avfoundation/documentation/AVFoundation/AVCaptureVideoDataOutput/alwaysDiscardsLateVideoFrames] property of [doc://com.apple.avfoundation/documentation/AVFoundation/AVCaptureVideoDataOutput] or the [doc://com.apple.avfoundation/documentation/AVFoundation/AVCaptureDepthDataOutput/alwaysDiscardsLateDepthData] property of [doc://com.apple.avfoundation/documentation/AVFoundation/AVCaptureDepthDataOutput] to choose whether the capture output discards data.

## Reasons

- **AVCaptureOutput.DataDroppedReason.none**: The system didn’t drop data.
- **AVCaptureOutput.DataDroppedReason.outOfBuffers**: The system dropped data because the capture output exhausted its internal pool of memory buffers.
- **AVCaptureOutput.DataDroppedReason.discontinuity**: The system dropped data because the device providing data experienced a discontinuity, and the output lost an unknown number of data objects.
